hi dirk,

i've been compiling RInside on windows with the new RTools based on GCC 
4.9. with stock settings, this all compiles successfully.

however, if i add "-std=c++11" to CXX_FLAGS, then the compilation fails. 
it chokes on line 27 of RInside.cpp [1]. what makes this more 
interesting is that this line is surrounded with an #ifndef WIN32, so 
this line shouldn't even be in there ( 
https://github.com/eddelbuettel/rinside/blob/master/src/RInside.cpp#L25 )

if i comment lines 26, 27 out, then the compilation works.

this isn't actually a new problem for me, i've been commenting out lines 
26, 27 for a couple of years now (my last toolchain was based on GCC 
4.8.2), but this is the first time i've had a simple reproducible example.

have you encountered this before?

with thanks

jonathon

